author: Varsha Seti
text:
Obtaining certificate by way of an unethical route is unacceptable and it looks so funny when some individuals (so called doctors) are defending such culprit on the ground that the way of arresting is unethical. let me tell you the legislature,the onus of the police is to tell arrestee why they are being put under arrest and  deliver a notice (or warrant)  before detention and same has been complied. Thre is no such rule to differ the arrest procedure once the warrant has been issued unless further WRITTEN notice is issued by the concerned authority.
Today we all Nepalese people saw the TV interview of the Doctor Jha, what he said has many bias statements, he said
1. where do such accuse will run away ? 
Ans: It is duty and right of police to take such accused person before a court. No defence on the ground ,where will they go.
2 .A baseless statement that clean Police should  investigate - / my questions is- had the police not been active in their role they would not have noticed  such fake and fraud doctors and pilots. (be aware all frauds of other professions also, your bad days is also coming soon)
Ans: Indeed Mr.Jha intention was to tell that  not only our hands are black there are other individuals, institutions, organisations etc that we share the same black roof, so let's have some amicable treaty. Please, doctor, you are not supposed to take trial on the health of the civilian of the nation.Yes ,we all support for clean in every profession like Doctor, Engineers, Advocates, Governmental services people indeed whole nation.
3.A journalist asked the question do the fraud doctor can play with the health issue of the Nepalese people? => Doctor jha replied , 
20 lacs was demanded by clean Nepalese Police in chabahil Kathmandu, and only later he said i am against fraud doctor. 
Ans: Kindly stop playing blame game by saying clean Nepalese Police. Nepalese people are also aware that many incidents has happened where there is bureaucracy of police department but this initiation made by police is fully appreciable.
4.He said that even tea stall people and ill people are saying whether he is a fake doctor or not?
Ans: Mr Jha, now Nepalese people are already   concious about what is right and what is wrong. We have very much right to talk about credentials and authenticity about a doctor. It is the national issue and health concern of every citizen. This scenario was caused by the lack of integrity and lack of ethical practice by the unqualified , fake, and fraud doctors and it is baseless to talk that Police has defamed the professionalism of doctor.
 In fact, for instance doing an operation of uterus instead of the stomach, similarly  carelessly leaving scissor inside the body of victims has already depicted the quality of doctors.

And one more request to doctor Jha, he is in the esteem profession and  he should  at least know how to speak politely,  and no debate is won by talking baselessly ,loudly and furiously.
You might be against fraud  but such type of defence  and conversations makes people think that your subconscious mind is to protect such fraud doctors.

Hence, the mission is to put fake and fraud doctors inside the bar, Not only the doctors every individual who has committed fraud to obtain the certificate, licence or any such document should be under the radar of Law and order. It should be noted that Knowlege without character has no respect in society.
